\h SAY \d

\uUSAGE\n
!say \s[\d#oadverb#c\s]\d \s[\d#ttarget\s]\d \s[\d#oadverb#c\s]\d utterance

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Say something out loud, such that everyone in your current room will hear you.
You may optionally provide a "target" so as to indicate that you are speaking directly to the specified individual.
Furthermore, you may optionally provide at most one "adverbial phrase" (in square brackets) so as to illustrate the manner in which you speak.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\qsay nice to meet you, too\d \r->\d You say, "Nice to meet you, too."4`
\qsay \l#t\qtaro nice to meet you, too\d \r->\d You say to Taro, "Nice to meet you, too."4`
\qsay \l#o\qquietly\l#c\q nice to meet you, too\d \r->\d You say quietly, "Nice to meet you, too."4`
\qsay \l#o\qquietly\l#c\q \l#t\qtaro nice to meet you, too\d \r->\d You say quietly to Taro, "Nice to meet you, too."4`
\qsay \l#t\qtaro \l#o\qwith some hesitation\l#c\q nice to meet you, too\d \r->\d You say to Taro with some hesitation, "Nice to meet you, too."4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
abbreviation, communication, link, telepathy, unlink, whisper
